# encoding: utf-8
=begin

Chrism Forge!
Helps clerics make chrisms and keep chrism gems organized.

Author: Mystienne

Contributor credits:
  Timbalt - chrism-maker automation and tracking
  Aethor - original script basis
  Leafiara - chrismable gem list (from PurifyL)
  Tatterclaws - chrism sort function (from chrismsort)

Who this is for:
  Chrism Forge is for clerics who make chrisms and for any character who wants to sort chrism gems.

What this script does:
  The setup window lets you pick containers from drop-down lists.
  The Chrismarium tab can fill your chrismarium from saved finished chrisms by selected quality.
  The Gemcutting tab can save a lapidary box and pick designs for chrism-run outcomes.
  Count Gems shows what gems are in the saved containers.
  Stage Gems quietly checks inventory and moves likely chrism gems into the gems-to-try container.
  Sort Chrisms looks for cobalt liquid and moves finished chrisms into the finished-chrism container.
  The main run casts 325 on each gem in the gems-to-try container, then moves successes and failures where they belong.
  If enabled in the Gemcutting tab, the run can cut each gem after it knows the outcome.
  If GemGuard has saved a gem's orb status and value, Chrism Forge can skip known non-orbs
  and orb gems under 3000 silver before spending mana on 325.
  When Chrism Forge makes a chrism, it saves that result back to GemGuard for later.
  Chrismarium mode pushes finished chrisms into your chrismarium instead of just storing them loose.
  Check Skills tells whether the current character can make chrisms and what retained-experience fullness they can make.
  The progress window shows a live status panel and can stop cleanly while keeping the report visible.

Important notes:
  A gem is only proven able to become a chrism after the script tries casting 325 on it.
  Cobalt liquid is how the script tells that a gem already has a chrism.
  The fullness wording shows retained experience and comes from Blessings ranks.
  The cobalt-liquid strength wording, like dull or bright, comes from gem value.
  GemGuard value help is used for known non-orbs and for orb gems that are too low value.

       author: Mystienne
  contributor: Timbalt, Aethor, Leafiara, Tatterclaws
         game: gs
      version: 0.12.4
        build: 07052026.7
         tags: cleric, chrism, utility, gtk
     required: Lich >= 5.11.0
        email: Mystienne@mystienne.com
      discord: Mystienne

=end

